Netherlands : socio-economic indicators 2014 - 2018

Netherlands

Introduction

The aim of this report is to present the economy and social conditions in 2014 - 2018 .

Our analysis will be divided on four areas using the following variables:

  • economy:
    • GDP per capita
    • Export as GDP percent
    • Import as GDP percent
    • RD as GDP percent - expenses on research and development expressed as % of GDP
  • Population:
    • population
    • birth rate
    • life expectation by 65
    • life expectation by birth
  • Unemployment:
    • unemployment rate
    • long term unemployment
  • Women situation:
    • fertility rate - number of children born pro 1000 people
    • age at 1st child - mean age of women when giving a birth to 1st child
    • gender pay gap - average difference between the remuneration for men and women who are working expressed in %

The dataset was obtained from Eurostat database.

GDP and the indicators dependent on it
year GDP_mld_dollars GDP.per.capita Export.as.GDP.percent Import.as.GDP.percent RD.as.GDP.percent
2014 670.14 39820 80.6 69.5 2.17
2015 688.37 40730 82.7 75.2 2.15
2016 706.16 41590 79.5 69.3 2.15
2017 736.04 43090 83.4 72.6 2.18
2018 771.77 44920 84.7 74.1 2.14

From the table below we can conclude, that the GDP in the period 2014 - 2018 has changed by 15.17%.

Taking into account the change of population by 2.09% such a change in absolute GDP corresponds to change in GDP per capita by 12.81%.

The maximum and minimum export expressed as GDP percent was observed in 2018 and in 2016 respectively.

The maximum and minimum import expressed as GDP percent was observed in 2015 and in 2016 respectively.
